---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Neutral problem gambling prevention information — for the public and prevention professionals alike."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="page-header__eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>About this site</h1>
      <p class="page-header__lead">
        Problem gambling prevention information — built to give the public and
        prevention professionals organized, trustworthy, state-specific
        information.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>Our mission</h2>
      <p>
        Help people understand gambling and gambling harm, connect quickly to free
        help, and give prevention professionals resources for all
        50 states, the District of Columbia, and five U.S. territories. The site's
        value is not original research — it is organized, accessible
        dissemination of an underused data layer, anchored to the National Problem
        Gambling Helpline, <strong>1-800-MY-RESET</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>Who it's for</h2>
      <p>
        Two audiences, one site: the <strong>general public</strong> — people who
        may be experiencing gambling harm, their families, and anyone seeking
        answers — and <strong>prevention professionals</strong>, including IC&amp;RC
        Prevention Specialists and the organizations they work with.
      </p>

      <h2>A neutral stance</h2>
      <p>
        We are neither for nor against the legalization of gambling. The goal is to
        be a trusted, neutral hub for prevention information — not an
        advocacy outlet.
      </p>

      <h2>How we source our data</h2>
      <p>
        Every state page is built from primary government sources, with each data
        point traceable to a citation. See
        <a href="/methodology">Methodology &amp; data sources</a> for the full
        approach, and <a href="/credits">Image credits</a> for the statehouse
        photo sources.
      </p>

      <h2>About the operator</h2>
      <p>
        This site is operated by a credentialed prevention specialist
        (OCPS, IC&amp;RC Prevention Specialist). <em>[Founder bio to be added.]</em>
      </p>

      <h2>Contact &amp; feedback</h2>
      <p>
        We welcome corrections and feedback, especially on data accuracy. A contact
        form is being added. <em>[Contact details to be added.]</em>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
